Local Variables:

1. BlockTime - int - sets the amount of time before another book can be spawned

2. DC - int - sets the Search DC for generating complete selection of books

3. NumberOfBooks - int - the total number of books on the shelf

4. spawnpoint - string - the tag of the way point where the book will spawn

5+. Book_X these are the index numbers of the books from the dynamic resource folder.

This script will spawn a chest at a randomly-selected waypoint within the area that this trigger is placed. It pulls all information from the variables set on the "lj_randchestspwn" trigger.

The Tag and the Resref of the chest-to-spawn must match in order to make sure duplicates don't appear. By default, the script uses the placeable chest lj_randchestspwn, but any chest can be used by setting the "resref" variable.

Variables
----------

string resref: The tag/resref of the chest to spawn and tag of waypoints 
int BlockTime: The cooldown from this trigger spawning a new chest
int OncePerReset: Setting 1 one will mean this fires 1/reset per player

int SearchDC: If set, this will require a search check to find chests
int LockedDC: If set, this will lock the chest and set an unlock DC

----------
If using a custom chest, you do not need the following variables. If using the default, these will enable you to set amount of loot and quality of loot:

int RandomLoot: defines the upper integer of how much random loot you want to spawn (i.e., putting in 3 would spawn 0-3 random loot pieces)

int FixedLoot: defines how much loot you always want spawned. This can be combined with RandomLoot

int LootLevel: defines which level of loot bin to be used. 1 is uber low, 3 is medium, 5 is uber, etc. Required - the chest will not work if LootLevel is not set from 1 to 5

float TimeLimit: defines how long it takes for the next batch of loot to spawn within the chest. This is in SECONDS (i.e. 60.0 = one minute ). If this is not set, it will default to the BlockTime.

This is the default waypoint you may place to set a patrol path for a creature or NPC.
1. Create the creature and either use its current Tag or fill in a new one.
2. Place or make sure the WalkWayPoints() is within the body of the On Spawn script for the creature.
3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.
